import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load groundwater quality data into a GeoDataFrame
gdf = gpd.read_file('D:/academic_project/geo_data_2019.gpkg')

# Filter data based on groundwater quality categories
desirable = gdf[gdf['Water_Quality'] == 0]
permissible = gdf[gdf['Water_Quality'] == 1]
non_potable = gdf[gdf['Water_Quality'] == 2]

# Load Tamil Nadu shapefile
tamilnadu = gpd.read_file('D:/academic_project/tamil-nadu_shp.shp')

# Create the plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))

# Plot Tamil Nadu map
tamilnadu.plot(ax=ax, color='lightpink', edgecolor='black')

# Plot points representing permissible, desirable, and non-potable well IDs
permissible.plot(ax=ax, color='green', markersize=5, label='Permissible')
desirable.plot(ax=ax, color='blue', markersize=5, label='Desirable')
non_potable.plot(ax=ax, color='red', markersize=5, label='Non-Potable')

# Get legend handles and labels
handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()

# Add legend with explicit handles and labels
ax.legend(handles, labels, loc='upper right')

# Add title and labels
plt.title('Groundwater Quality Map - Tamil Nadu Year 2019')
plt.xlabel('Longitude')
plt.ylabel('Latitude')

# Show the plot
plt.show()
